Question 2: Spring Boot Data JPA – Student College Management System (@ManyToOne)
Scenario

Develop a Spring Boot application for a College Management System where multiple Students belong to one College. Establish a Many-to-One relationship using Spring Data JPA.

Navigation should be possible only from Student to College.

College
Field	Type
collegeId	Long
collegeName	String
city	String

Student
Field	Type
studentId	Long
studentName	String
branch	String
percentage	Double
college	College

Relationship
Use @ManyToOne in Student.
Use @JoinColumn(name="college_id").
Do not create @OneToMany in College.
Use CascadeType.ALL.
Relationship should be Unidirectional.

Requirements
Create College and Student entities.
Configure Many-to-One mapping.
Save multiple Students under one College.
Retrieve Student details with College details.
Use Repository.

Display output using CommandLineRunner.
